<!-- ================= HOW TO USE ================= -->
<div class="pagebreak"></div>
<h1 id="howto">How to use this manual</h1>
<p class="intro">This is your day-to-day reference. Read your team's section fully once, then keep this open while you work.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Find your job.</b> Use the Table of Contents to jump to your team's section (Courses, Content/LMS, Webinars, Payments, Finance, Students).</li>
<li><b>Follow steps in order.</b> Every procedure is a numbered list — do <b>one action per step</b>. On-screen words are shown <b>in bold</b> so you can match them to the screen.</li>
<li><b>Use the direct links.</b> Each procedure starts with a <span class="quick">🔗 Quick link</span> line. Copy that web address into your browser to land on the right page. Some links contain a placeholder like <span class="url">[COURSE-ID]</span> — that means "the long code in the address bar for that specific item" (you get there by clicking the item, explained in each step).</li>
<li><b>Check your work.</b> Every procedure ends with a green <span class="check">✅ How to check it worked</span> box. Don't skip it.</li>
<li><b>Avoid mistakes.</b> Orange <span class="warn">⚠️ Common mistakes</span> boxes warn you before something goes wrong.</li>
<li><b>Know your limits.</b> Blue <span class="who">WHO can do this</span> boxes state exactly which staff role is allowed. If a button is missing for you, your role does not have that permission — that is normal and safe.</li>
<li><b>Screenshots.</b> Where you see <span class="shot">[SCREENSHOT: …]</span>, that's a placeholder for a picture to be pasted in later.</li>
</ul>
<p class="small">Note on roles: the portal's real roles are <b>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Content Editor, Current Affairs Editor, Support / Operations, Finance / Revenue,</b> and <b>Viewer / Analyst</b>. Throughout this manual, "Course team / Content team / Webinar team" map to <b>Content Editor</b> or <b>Content Admin</b>; "Payment team / Finance team" map to <b>Finance / Revenue</b> (or Admin); "Support" maps to <b>Support / Operations</b>.</p>

