<!-- ================= WHO CAN DO WHAT ================= -->
<div class="pagebreak"></div>
<h1 id="whocan">Who Can Do What</h1>
<p class="intro">The portal uses fixed permissions bundled into roles. A staff member only sees menus and buttons their role allows. This is enforced both in the screen (hidden) and on the server (rejected), so it is safe.</p>

<h3>The eight built-in roles</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>What they can do</th><th>What they cannot do</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Super Admin</b></td><td>Everything — content, revenue, payments, settings, staff and roles. Only role that can reverse/edit/delete payments and empty Payment Trash.</td><td>Cannot be deleted (at least one must always exist).</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Admin</b></td><td>Full operations including revenue &amp; payments, content, settings and managing staff.</td><td>Cannot edit the roles &amp; permission matrix; cannot manage Super Admins.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Content Admin</b></td><td>All content (Courses, Webinars, Quizzes, Current Affairs, PDFs), SEO, publishing, settings, students &amp; leads, non-revenue analytics, SMS.</td><td>No revenue, payments or pricing; no staff/roles.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Content Editor</b></td><td>Create, edit and publish all content; manage SEO.</td><td>No revenue/payments; no settings, staff or roles.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Current Affairs Editor</b></td><td>Only Current Affairs — articles, daily/monthly, PDFs, CA categories &amp; tags; publish CA.</td><td>No other content modules; no revenue, settings or staff.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Support / Operations</b></td><td>View &amp; manage students, leads and enrollments; non-revenue analytics; send SMS.</td><td>No publishing; no revenue; no staff.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Finance / Revenue</b></td><td>Revenue dashboards, manage payments/invoices/payouts, edit pricing &amp; plans.</td><td>No content; no staff, roles or settings.</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Viewer / Analyst</b></td><td>Read-only across allowed modules; non-revenue analytics.</td><td>No edits; no revenue; no staff/settings.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Task-by-permission map</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Task area</th><th>Permission required</th><th>Roles that have it</th></tr>
<tr><td>Create / edit Courses &amp; Content/LMS</td><td>Manage course content</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Content Editor</td></tr>
<tr><td>Create / edit Webinars</td><td>Manage webinars &amp; events</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Content Editor</td></tr>
<tr><td>Brochure / PDF library</td><td>Manage PDFs &amp; media</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Content Editor, Current Affairs Editor</td></tr>
<tr><td>Publish / unpublish content</td><td>Publish / unpublish content</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Content Editor, Current Affairs Editor</td></tr>
<tr><td>View Payments &amp; Finance, Course EMI &amp; Seats, Access at Risk, Duplicate Enrollments</td><td>View revenue dashboards</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Finance / Revenue</td></tr>
<tr><td>Approve / reject payments, upload proof, re-verify</td><td>Manage payments</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Finance / Revenue</td></tr>
<tr><td>Reverse / edit / delete a payment, Payment Trash</td><td>Super Admin only</td><td>Super Admin</td></tr>
<tr><td>Edit pricing &amp; Subscription Plans</td><td>Edit pricing &amp; plans</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Finance / Revenue</td></tr>
<tr><td>Add / edit students, manual enroll, login codes</td><td>Manage students, leads &amp; enrollments</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Support / Operations</td></tr>
<tr><td>Add / manage staff &amp; grant comp access</td><td>Manage staff accounts</td><td>Super Admin, Admin</td></tr>
<tr><td>Create / edit roles &amp; permission matrix</td><td>Manage roles &amp; permissions</td><td>Super Admin</td></tr>
<tr><td>Website settings, Home, Toppers, Navigation, About</td><td>Manage settings</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin</td></tr>
<tr><td>Send SMS &amp; view SMS logs</td><td>Send SMS</td><td>Super Admin, Admin, Content Admin, Support / Operations</td></tr>
</table>
<p class="small">Anti-escalation rule: when creating roles or staff, you can only grant permissions you yourself hold. You can never give someone more power than you have.</p>

<!-- ================= SECTION 1 ================= -->
<div class="pagebreak"></div>
<h1 id="s1">1. Access &amp; Accounts</h1>
<p class="intro">This section covers signing in, what every menu does, and (for managers) creating and controlling staff logins. Get comfortable here first — everything else builds on it.</p>
<div class="quick">🔗 Quick link — Admin portal: <span class="url">https://namanias.com/admin</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Staff &amp; Roles: <span class="url">https://namanias.com/admin/staff</span></div>

<h2 id="s1-1">1.1 How to log in to the admin portal</h2>
<div class="who"><b>WHO:</b> Any staff member who has been given an admin username and password.</div>
<ol>
<li>Open your browser and go to <span class="url">https://namanias.com/admin</span>.</li>
<li>On the <b>Admin Panel</b> sign-in card, type your <b>Username</b>.</li>
<li>Type your <b>Password</b>.</li>
<li>Click <b>Sign in →</b>.</li>
<li>Wait for the dashboard to load. The left menu shows only the sections your role allows.</li>
</ol>
<span class="shot">[SCREENSHOT: the Admin Panel login card showing the Username field, Password field, and the "Sign in →" button.]</span>
<div class="check">✅ How to check it worked: you see the left-hand menu (Dashboard, etc.) and, in the top-right corner, your username with a coloured role badge (e.g. "Admin").</div>
<div class="warn">⚠️ Common mistakes: usernames are all lowercase; extra spaces fail. If you just got a temporary password, you'll see an orange "please change your temporary password" banner — change it (see 1.3).</div>

<h2 id="s1-2">1.2 If you can't log in / forgot password / got logged out</h2>
<div class="who"><b>WHO:</b> Any staff member. Password resets are done by a manager (Super Admin / Admin).</div>
<h4>You were logged out automatically</h4>
<p>Sessions stay signed in for <b>7 days</b> of inactivity and roll forward while you work. After 7 idle days you're signed out gracefully. Just sign in again (1.1).</p>
<h4>Wrong username or password</h4>
<ol>
<li>Re-type carefully (lowercase username, no spaces).</li>
<li>If it still says <b>"Invalid credentials."</b>, your password may have changed or your account may be <b>Disabled</b>.</li>
<li>Ask a manager to check your account and, if needed, reset your password (1.7). <b>There is no self-service "Forgot password" link</b> — a manager must reset it for you.</li>
</ol>
<div class="check">✅ How to check it worked: after a manager resets you, sign in with the new temporary password, then set your own (1.3).</div>
<div class="warn">⚠️ Common mistakes: don't keep retrying the same wrong password — contact a manager. If your role was changed, some menus may disappear; that is expected, not an error.</div>

<h2 id="s1-3">1.3 How to change your own password</h2>
<div class="who"><b>WHO:</b> Any signed-in staff member.</div>
<ol>
<li>Sign in at <span class="url">https://namanias.com/admin</span>.</li>
<li>In the top bar, click <b>Password</b>.</li>
<li>Enter your current and new password in the <b>Change password</b> box and confirm.</li>
<li>If you logged in with a temporary password, also use the orange banner's <b>Change password</b> button.</li>
</ol>
<div class="check">✅ How to check it worked: the orange "temporary password" banner disappears; next sign-in uses your new password.</div>

